For the ice cream, mix the purée with the sugar and then stir in the cream.Place the mixture in an ice cream machine and churn according to manufacturer’s instructions until frozen.For the strawberries, cut the strawberries in half and sprinkle with the sugar, basil and balsamic vinegar.Gently mix to coat the strawberries in the mixture and leave for 20 minutes, or until you see the strawberries start to soften and cure in the sugar and vinegar.To serve, divide the strawberries and the liquid into two bowls.Scoop over the strawberry ice cream, sprinkle with the crumbled amoretti biscuits and garnish with the basil cress.